



Lijordet is a station on Røabanen of the Oslo T-bane system between Østerås (station)|Østerås and Eiksmarka, 9.6 km from Stortinget. It is the second of three stations on Røabanen within the Bærum municipality, and passengers travelling here from Oslo need to pay a higher fare.

The station was opened on December 22 1948 when Røabanen was expanded from Røa (station)|Røa to Lijordet;[http://www.sporveien.no/templates/Page____1033.aspx T-bane stations in the west];.
